reviews_data.review_text: Great little pick me up beside Harris Teeter today!

This place is awesome! Customer service is always great. I am always greeted with a smile and plenty of recommendations when I need them! I’ve loved everything I’ve ordered here and would recommend it to anyone.
Really high quality coffee and teas. Consistently  great service.

10/10 best coffee of my life! Barista was super friendly and has a no cost cut modern vibes. I didn't know my entire life decisions was all meant to have this coffee! Whom ever marries that barista is the luckiest man alive cuz she makes expresso heaven, not coffee... changed my life.
My barista was very nice. My coffee was great!
Awesome experience. Try the double shot Dirty Chai. Was just by and the staff was on point today and drinks in my hand pretty darn quick. Try them out.
Coffee was great and the service was greater, Kimb makes a great cup of coffee
Kim hit me up with the bro-tachio. That be bussin fo real fo real
This shop is so cute! I love the atmosphere, very quiet and peaceful for doing schoolwork. Kimberly was so kind and had great customer service!

The coffee here is A+, there is plenty of variety and most of the staff are super friendly and knowledgeable. One of the baristas, a young redheaded woman, is curt and cold. I avoid the shop when I see her working.
This is a cute location that is tucked away from busier areas.  The service was friendly and inviting.   I would highly recommend this location to others.

It was amazing from food and service, our barista was amazing as well, we got there with 10+ people and she handled our order perfectly she’s the ginger head , Eden, thank you so much. If you’re visiting it’s highly recommended:)

Beautiful coffee shop the barista was very friendly and helpful. Love the feeling as you walk in to the shop and the fact that the coffee is crafted and not sitting in a pot waiting to be served. I bought coffee for my coworkers and I can say with confidence we will be back for more.

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: First time visit, service was amazing. blueberry muffin was amazing warmed up and the shaken espresso that was made was perfect. Will be coming back for sure!
Laney the barista is a breath of fresh air. Super friendly and knows what she is talking about. She also is super flexible and accommodating to what the customer wants!

This is a great location. Kind baristas that can make delicious drinks and recommendations. Love the muffins. Peaceful atmosphere that is great for sitting and sipping and getting some work done. Very clean. Also appreciate the hours, open early even on Sundays.

The atmosphere was very cool and the staff were very knowledgeable. They helped me pick what I wanted when I really had no clue and I loved my recommendation. The prices were better than their competitors for a higher quality product.
Awesome, this area needed an Alternative to the same old crap coffee shop.

I absolutely love Waterbean. Every time I have been there the service and atmosphere has been outstanding. The coffee is always hot and so good. Have had an affogato and it is SO delicious. Love the coconut almond ice cream. I am so thankful for this location here in Denver. Is very convenient.

If you're looking for cheap caffeine, this place probably isn't your cup of tea, but if you're looking for good coffee and a clean, quiet place to sit, this is a good place for it. There's a lot of options for the coffee being served, as well as teas. Overall, a nice treat!

Laney went above and beyond to make me the most delicious sweet sugar-free latte. Due to my type diabetes, I have to be extremely careful about what I drink, and she was so accommodating. My wife also got a copy here she loved, and my kids loved the baba drinks she made them.

This was an amazing first experience at this coffee shop and we will definitely be back. We’ve been to certain other coffee shops in the area but never received the service at this level. Can’t wait till our next visit
I was hesitant because of the negative review but happy I tried it. My new favorite local spot!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Brooklyn! The negative reviews are all fake from a local competitor and our attorney are working behind the scene to bring a lawsuit soon. Thank you so much for your support!

reviews_data.review_text: Very pleasant service and great coffee. Highly recommend this great little coffee shop.
All around an amazing little shop! I come here on my breaks and to study and the people are always so friendly and welcoming. Highly recommend!

Great Customer Service, very clean, good ambiance. Ordered a pour over coffee, which was done correctly and with care. Great Job! Love seeing small coffee shops that care and take the time to make things right.

Stopped by to see the new spot! Have always liked Waterbean Coffee. The Waterbean in Huntersville is one of my favorite places to go.

We wanted to support the opening of the Denver cafe. The baristas were incredibly kind and easy to talk to. The atmosphere is so clean and inviting. It is cozy and small but the chairs are wicked comfortable. This is a perfect place to grab coffee, sit and chat with a date, have a business meeting, study, or to play board games.

I asked the baristas to make me a hot caramel latte not to sweet and my date got the s'mores iced drink with cold foam. My latte was perfect! The s'mores cold foam actually tasted like toasted marshmallow. It even had the texture of melted marshmallow. Not sure how you guys did that but it's tasty.

Prices are fair and waterbean has amazing coffee beans. They also featured a one of a kind Colombia coffee for sale to take home with you. It is an award winning lot of beans so don't miss out!

Welcome to Denver and I hope you guys do so well.
Coffee and muffin were great! Staff was super nice

Hands down some of the best coffee and service I’ve received. I have visited multiple Waterbean locations and have ALWAYS been impressed with the quality, aesthetic, and customer service. I always recommend Waterbean over any other coffee shop to anyone I know who appreciates GOOD coffee!

I love Waterbean and am so disappointed to see other people going after them. The coffee is always enjoyable and I appreciate that they always have a gluten free pastry/bakery option for me. Hoping you all can get to the bottom of what’s happening and get back to just making great coffee in a lovely atmosphere. We are glad to have you close by!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Virginia! We really appreciate this from the bottom of our hearts!

reviews_data.review_text: What a wonderful experience I had the other day! Coffee was wonderful, our barista was so kind and the atmosphere was fantastic. Will gladly be back!
Love waterbean! My fave is the macadamia nut milk in a hot latte! Not your average run of the mill coffee shop! These people know coffee!
Lovely spot to meet for a chat!  Cappuccino was perfect.
Amazing. I LOVE the iced chai. Clean and friendly environment. Fast service. Love it.
Went to Waterbean Coffee for the first time to try something new and it was a really good experience, had really good coffee!

Love their space, seating, and drink selection!! We walked in the other day and made a request off menu and the barista created a wonderful drink for us!!! Also, the hours are great! Finally, Denver has an option for a great after dinner cappuccino!

I love Water Bean! I used to go to the one in Huntersville all the time but ever since the one in Denver opened, it’s cut my study commute in half. Theres great drinks, kind baristas  and good seating. Would highly recommend to try it out:)
I love this new spot. So chic and calm. My latte was delicious. Will definitely be back!

I hate to see robots and or Karen's put up bad reviews for local businesses.  Lets support those local and if you have a concern talk through it with the business; as part of their business is customer service.
I have only had a coffee or hot chocolate but each time it has been tasty and served with a smile.
Coffee is good, lots of different flavors to choose from, love having different coffee places to choose from depending on your vibe in sweet little denver♡
Great coffee! Staff was friendly and the space is beautiful!
Have been here twice so far with great experiences! This will definitely be a new staple coffee shop for me.

Recently moved to the Denver area from Cornelius and was a regular at the Cornelius location. So happy when you moved to the Denver area! The shop has such a cute atmosphere both indoors and out and cannot beat the coffee! All the staff has been wonderful and kind.

Water bean coffee is such a treat to visit! I have been there twice in the past week to meet friends and the atmosphere is so cool , the coffee and treats are amazing. The macaroons are beautiful and the staff is so friendly! Highly recommend!!
Hands down best coffee in Denver!
Delicious coffee and pastries! The service is excellent and the atmosphere of the shop is lovely! It isn’t noisy inside, but very relaxing. I love the little outdoor seating area too.

I’m so happy to have Waterbean near us now! Black coffee is my #1 choice (and theirs is awesome!) but sometimes I want an iced coffee. Waterbean is the only local/small business place I’ve had that actually makes a good iced coffee. It’s creamy and flavorful but  you can still totally taste the coffee! Most other places I’ve tried make them too watery and with the weakest flavor ever. They also make an amazing brown butter rice krispy treat 🤤 Last but not least, their aesthetic is perfection. Absolutely gorgeous and always clean! Please give them a try if you haven’t already! I’ve been to 3 other locations of theirs and they are all consistently just as good!

I've always had enjoyable experiences at Waterbean, friendly staff, good baked goods, great coffee! If you've never tried it, you're missing out. Love having so many locations in and around Charlotte now! Time to replace Starbucks!
The coffee is amazing and the staff are very kind and friendly. It's a beautiful shop with a very nice outdoor seating area.
Cute shop with knowledgeable baristas and a friendly vibe. Espresso based drinks had wonderful extraction with notes of chocolate and hint of dulce de leche.
Calm environment, great coffee, great staff. Recommend to anyone looking for a local coffee spot!

Stopped in after a fasting doctor appointment to get a dose of caffeine. It was my first time at Waterbean and it was a very pleasant surprise. I usually drink a latte, or a regular American coffee, but this time I thought I'd try something a little different. I went off menu and got a hot nonfat latte with white chocolate and raspberry. I usually sweeten my coffee but don't like it overly sweet, and this was a perfect balance and so delicious! I also got an oatmeal apple breakfast cookie which was excellent! Overall, I enjoyed my time at Waterbean. The shop is nice with a quiet atmosphere, music playing lightly in the background with tables both inside and outside under cover. It's clean and welcoming and the staff is friendly and attentive. Highly recommend stopping in for your daily brew, whether it's coffee or tea.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place for coffee, food, atmosphere and service.
The seating area was cramped, and the noise level made it hard to enjoy my coffee. I prefer a quieter, more comfortable environment.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are a local business committed to doing the right thing, offering the best service and products that set us apart from our competitors. Unfortunately, some of them have resorted to writing fake 1-star reviews in an attempt to slander and harm our reputation. We are actively investigating this matter, as we have evidence suggesting they are also using automated bots to inflate their own ratings with fake 5-star reviews. Rest assured, we will take all legal measures available to protect our business and ensure fairness.

reviews_data.review_text: The café served exceptional coffee and had highly skilled baristas. Their freshly baked pastries were a delight, and we were even lucky enough to watch them being delivered. Their extensive tea selection was impressive, and the café itself was charming, with an outdoor seating area.
Love waterbean!  Great flavor to their coffees and the atmosphere just makes your day!!
Awesome coffee only outdone by the fantastic service and friendly atmosphere!

Amazing coffee! Friendly staff, beautiful place that is really well lit! They even have an adorable spot outside to enjoy the sun & lovely weather while having my coffee! They have a great range of coffees, from different countries & in different roasts! their tea selection leaves nothing to desire with multiple selections of each kind of tea.
This place is a must see when you're in the area, especially if you're familiar with the Waterbean brand!

review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Dietary restrictions, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: Everyone is so nice every time I come! They are always willing to give advice on what to try and what’s good together. Plus there are tons of Gluten Free and vegan options!!!
Glad to have Waterbean in our community! Great location and great coffee!

Waterbean Coffee is a true gem in the coffee scene. From the moment you walk in, you're greeted with a warm, inviting atmosphere that feels both modern and cozy. The interior is thoughtfully designed, with comfortable seating options and plenty of natural light, making it an ideal spot for working, meeting friends, or simply relaxing with a good book.

The coffee here is nothing short of exceptional. Each cup is brewed to perfection, with a rich, smooth flavor that clearly comes from high-quality beans and expert baristas. Whether you prefer a classic espresso, a creamy latte, or one of their unique specialty drinks, you won't be disappointed. I highly recommend trying their signature pour-over; it's a revelation in how good coffee can taste.

But Waterbean Coffee is more than just great coffee. Their selection of pastries and light bites is equally impressive. Freshly baked and delicious, there's something for everyone, whether you're in the mood for something sweet or savory.

The staff at Waterbean Coffee truly sets this place apart. They are knowledgeable, friendly, and genuinely passionate about what they do. They go out of their way to make every visit enjoyable, offering personalized recommendations and making sure you have everything you need.

In addition, the location is fantastic. Whether you're a local or just passing through, it's conveniently situated and offers a peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of daily life.

Overall, Waterbean Coffee is an outstanding coffee shop that excels in every aspect. Great coffee, delicious food, a wonderful ambiance, and top-notch service make it a must-visit. Five stars all the way!
The atmosphere was beautiful & clean and the service was excellent. I ordered a caramel frappuccino and it tasted delicious! 10/10 will be back again :))
So happy denver finally has a waterbean!! Went the other day and my latte was just like the one I used to drive to cornelius for 🙌😍
